You have been provided with a complete simulation for a simple clonal breeding 
program. You are tasked with increasing genetic gain by finding a better 
strategy for selecting parents and/or crosses when developing F1s. You cannot 
change any other aspect of the breeding program. 

You can use the phenotypes in the pheno slot and the pedigree in SP to aid in 
parent selection. Feel free to modify the simulation script to store historic 
phenotypes if you so choose. 

You can change the number of crosses (nCrosses) and the number of seedlings 
(nSeedlings), but nCrosses times nSeedlings must equal 1000.

You may not use the true genetic values in gv or the genotypes to aid in 
selecting parents. We are assuming these are unknown.